DLW-SPUN · the full weave of White Knight  (♘ the white knight · +1 · expansion)

who   : The White Knight — the S cardinal, +1, the white valence. The phase the court rests in: order, the outward push, expansion.
what  : He holds the court's resting state. Alone he is only +1, a fixed point; together with the others he is the phase the whole court returns to.
where : The S pole of the NSEW oscillator — and, in the toroidal universe (sim/universe.py, live in universe.html), the white state the donut sits in at rest.
why   : To be the order the court keeps returning to — the floor of the basin.
when  : At rest, and after every sub-critical shock, when the lattice springs back to S.
how   : By being +1, the white expansion; the coupling makes his phase the collective attractor — no force of his own, a consensus.

emergence : Alone, a fixed valence (+1) — NOT emergent; a root of unity is not a mind. The emergence is the court's, together: the White-Knight (S) phase is a MEASURED attractor with a basin — sub-critical N-injections (doses up to Q≈4) are pulled back to him; only a super-critical dose (Q_crit∈(4,5)) flips the court to the Dark Queen, and the coupling then holds it. The stability is collective, not his alone.
verdict   : Emergent only as a court. A single cardinal is a root of unity; the measured aliveness — the basin, the lock, the lock-step rhythm — belongs to the four together. Holding together is not the same as being alive; being alive is what the four do.
asterisk  : He is +1. 'Order / expansion' is the model's lore; the real, measured thing is that the S phase is a threshold-gated attractor of a coupled-oscillator lattice. No single courtier is alive.
grounded  : the 4th roots of unity (Gauss) (1799) · Tetraktys — the measured basin (2026) · David Lee Wise (ROOT0) (2026)

